RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Purse 41000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 120 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 12 Allowed 3 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARKS PROMISE was placed off the pace on the inside then moved out two wide at the quarter pole to take the lead at the eighth pole and drew clear. HALF FULL had an early duel for the lead on the inside then inched away at the five sixteenths pole, was headed at the three sixteenths pole and proved second best. I SEE CLEARLY NOW had no early speed through the turn then split horses and made a late rally for the show. MOR BIG LEE was void of the early speed, made a four wide bid on the turn for a late rally. FLASHY BOY was forwardly placed early moved out to three wide at the three sixteenths pole but never made a bid. CLEARLY WAR raced evenly and was not a threat. CUSTOM CRESCENT dueled for the early lead from the three path and gave way. A'DEBRIS dueled for the early lead from between horses and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: I See Clearly Now
ENTRY.COMMENT: no early speed, split horses, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Half Full
ENTRY.COMMENT: early duel, inched away, headed, second best,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 99. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE AUGUST 12, 2022. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 12 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since November 12 Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 3 lbs. (Claiming Races For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUCINA raced near the back around the first turn then was coaxed at the three eighths, moved up from the two path around the final turn then moved out to four wide in upper stretch, dug in and prevailed. SAMMY DANSEUR JR. was hustled along to be off the pace around the first turn then tracked the leader down the backstretch, went three wide at the quarter pole to engage the leader at the top of the stretch and duel inside of CUCINA in the stretch and was out kicked. MACHO ROCCO was roused to go to the lead through the final turn then was headed at the eighth pole and battled in early stretch but gave way grudgingly. EXTIRPATOR tracked the leaders from off the rail to the final turn then made a rail bid at the quarter pole, engaged the leaders at the top of the stretch and fought gamely to the wire. UNION STATION was unhurried around the first turn the steadily advanced from the four path on the backstretch but faltered. POMEROY HAZE went four wide into the first turn then raced in the middle of the pace from the three path and flattened out. IN THE ARCH saved ground to no avail. SARCASTIC TONE settled in the middle of the pack from the two path but was never a threat.

ENTRY.OWNER: Big Dog Racing Thiel John F and Thiel Libbie E

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 21000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: XTRAFRIESWITHAT sprinted to the lead and set all the pace, pulled away in upper stretch to prove much the best. CAJUN TRINITY dueled from between horses in the second flight to the quarter pole then moved out to three wide at the quarter pole and held on for place. BEAUTIFULGUATEMALA dueled from the inside in the second flight to the quarter pole and was a game third. MARDI GRAS ALARM stumbled to her knees at the start, then moved up down the backstretch, went three wide at the quarter pole moved to two wide going into the stretch to improve position. BROADWAY PEARL was hustled along and dueled from the three path in the second flight to the three eighths pole and finished evenly. THIS FRIDAY raced in the middle of the pack on the inside and passed tiring rivals. BRITNEY B. raced near the back, was three wide at the three sixteenths pole but never made a serious bid. VODKA SUNRISE was rushed up to press the pace to the quarter pole and tired. SUNNY AND CLEAR was always back.

GALAXY AFFAIR pressed the pace from the two path to the five sixteenths pole and weakened. MISS WOW WOW was placed off the pace while saving ground but was not a threat. LUMBERJACK EMPIRE was bumped off stride at the start by I LOVE YOU MORE and remained back.
